<TITLE> Tit for tat on RMG factory supervisors </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, June 12 (bdnews24.com)  Two supervisors of a garment factory were assaulted by their former workers on Saturday. Around 10 were injured in the clash that erupted between workers of two factories at Savar's Khagan area on Saturday morning. Apparel Village's manager Mohammed Mukul said that two of their supervisors Jahid Hossain and Rokon were beaten up when they were entering the factory at around 8am. When workers of the factory moved to stop the assaulters  workers of Mozart Knitwear  they were also beaten up. Around 10 were injured including two officials. Jahid and Rokon were admitted to the local hospital. However, the workers alleged that a number of Apparel Village workers recently shifted to Mozart Knitwear as they were not being paid on time. The supervisors were threatening them in various manners to bring them back to the factory. They also beat up one of their co-workers, who refused to return to the factory. The workers, agitated by the incident, beat up the supervisors. Ashulia police chief Shirajul Islam said that the situation was under control with sufficient personnel deployed in front of both the factories. bdn
